Job Description
Why Halliburton? How about global opportunities, interesting work within small cohesive teams, extensive training, and the opportunity to take your career wherever you want it to GO, with all the support and stability of a truly global organization. With more than 72,000 employees in approximately 80 countries, Halliburton is one of the largest and most respected energy services companies in the industry. Since 1919, our customers have relied on our industry-leading technologies, scientific expertise and, most importantly, our knowledgeable and experienced professionals to help them meet the world's demand for energy. Whether you are a new graduate seeking your first job, or an experienced professional looking to make a career change, we have fantastic opportunities across our organization. Are you ready to GO?Seeking an HSE leader with proven best-in-class training and leadership skills within manufacturing environments. Role directly reports to Center Manager of Casing Equipment and is matrixed to Global HSE Manufacturing Manager.This high visibility position has the opportunity to lead HSE within a high growth facility that is less than a year old. Successful candidate will use technical and leadership competencies to drive continuous improvement. -Under general direction, will build, lead, direct and supervise staff of HSE professionals in the implementation of HSE programs, processes and strategies over a defined physical plant and location, with the potential to increase scope of responsibility-Coordinates the delivery of HSE products and services to operations and shared services personnel, in support of business acquisition and execution-Interfaces and negotiates with regulatory bodies, clients and subcontractors. Expected to be the HSE subject matter expert. -Frequently interfaces with peers, subordinates and operations personnel. Participates on teams, as well as work under own initiative-Expected to provide supervision and leadership to entry level
as well as experienced employees-Must be fully informed of HSE programs and strategies, and also informed on the Company's business strategies and HSE needs-Keeps informed of changes in business and regulatory requirements that may necessitate -Expected to engage in personnel development and other administrative activities, as well as make presentations and participate in conferences and industry associations Education and Experience:Bachelor's Degree in Occupational Health and Safety, Industrial Hygiene, Environmental Science, Biology, Engineering, or Business and 3-5 years comprehensive HSE experience within manufacturing environments required.-Experience in a leadership role with direct reports preferred-Graduate level degree strongly preferred-Must be able to demonstrate experience in understanding OSHA standards (Part 1903) regulating OSHA inspections, citations, and penalties, as well as specific standards for reporting and recording OSHA-recordable injuries and illnesses (Part 1904). -Preferably has experience and can demonstrate OSHA standards regulating various types of work environments and activities, including but not limited to, General Industry businesses (Part 1910, affecting most manufacturing, service industries, warehouses and distribution centers, and the medical / dental fields) -Experience with Lean Six Sigma principles and working in related environment preferred -Professional registrations or certifications such as CIH, CSP, or Lean Six Sigma related certification
and training preferredCompetencies:-Proven experience managing and leading teams of both exempt and non-exempt employees required-People leader who can oversee multiple projects in a fast paced environment, adapt to shifting priorities, and be very detail oriented-Effective and transferable project management methods and skill sets-Effective collaborator who builds relationships and drives results while working with multiple stakeholders in a matrix organizationLI-NB1Halliburton is proud to be an equal opportunity employer.
